[task]
title: Port MigrationsTest::Schema::EventSmallDT to DBIO::Test::Schema so t/30-datetime-mssql.t works
description: 
t/30-datetime-mssql.t in dbio-mssql calls `DBIO::Test::Schema->load_classes('EventSmallDT')` but the EventSmallDT schema class only exists at `dbio/t/lib/MigrationsTest/Schema/EventSmallDT.pm`. This causes a hard test failure: "Can't locate DBIO/Test/Schema/EventSmallDT.pm in @INC".

The fix is to port MigrationsTest::Schema::EventSmallDT to DBIO::Test::Schema::EventSmallDT, following the same pattern as the recent ArtistGUID port.

Source file: /storage/raid/home/getty/dev/perl/dbio-dev/dbio/t/lib/MigrationsTest/Schema/EventSmallDT.pm

The ported class should:
- Live at lib/DBIO/Test/Schema/EventSmallDT.pm
- Inherit from DBIO::Test::BaseResult
- Define the same columns and relationships as the source

The class must also be registered in DBIO::Test::Schema's load_classes() call.

This was discovered while running live integration tests against MSSQL 2022 in k3s (dbio-mssql). Other tests in the same suite pass after the recent fixes, but t/30 fails at load_classes time.
